The paper is about applying deep neural networks for ranking in search engines, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are common in machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL), suggesting cs.LG and cs.AI as likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses social media documents, which often contain images and videos, indicating cs.CV as a possible sub-category.
